---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import GetInTouchBanner from "../../components/common/GetInTouchBanner.tsx";
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<BaseLayout title="Fire Safety Emergency Drill - BBSD">
  <main>
    <article class="bg-white py-20">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-[800px] px-6">
        <p class="mb-4 text-sm text-gray-light">Aug 27, 2025</p>
        <h1 class="mb-8 text-3xl font-bold text-dark md:text-5xl">
          BBSD (Jiangsu Nantong) Engineering Technology Co., Ltd. Successfully
          Holds Fire Safety Emergency Drill
        </h1>

        <img
          src={`${base}images/news/fire-drill.jpg`}
          alt="Fire Safety Emergency Drill"
          loading="lazy"
          class="mb-10 w-full rounded-xl object-cover"
        />

        <div
          class="prose max-w-none space-y-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-gray"
        >
          <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-dark">
            Fortifying Safety Through Drills, Enhancing Skills Via Practical
            Training
          </h2>

          <p>
            To thoroughly implement the work safety policy of "Safety First,
            Prevention First, Comprehensive Management", comprehensively improve
            employees' fire safety awareness and emergency response
            capabilities, and build a solid "firewall" for the company's work
            safety, Best (Jiangsu Nantong) Engineering Technology Co., Ltd.
            successfully held a fire safety emergency drill in its office park
            on the morning of August 27.
          </p>

          <p>
            With "simulating real scenarios and testing practical response
            capabilities" as the core, this drill covered the entire process of
            fire early warning, emergency response, personnel evacuation, and
            fire-fighting rescue, further consolidating the foundation of the
            company's work safety management.
          </p>

          <p>
            To ensure the drill was efficient, orderly and close to real
            emergency situations, the company formulated a detailed plan in
            advance: the General Affairs Department, in collaboration with
            various departments, clarified the division of responsibilities,
            defined evacuation routes and emergency assembly points, prepared
            materials such as fire extinguishers and first-aid kits.
          </p>

          <p>
            <strong>Rapid Early Warning and Emergency Plan Activation:</strong> After
            the "fire" broke out on site, the first discoverer immediately pressed
            the manual fire alarm button and reported to the company's emergency command
            team. The command team quickly verified the situation, activated the fire
            safety emergency plan, and issued evacuation instructions.
          </p>

          <p>
            <strong>Orderly Evacuation and Accurate First Aid:</strong> Evacuation
            personnel guided employees to evacuate quickly by covering their mouths
            and noses with wet towels and bending down. All safely arrived at the
            designated assembly area within 5 minutes. The emergency team leader then
            counted the number of people to confirm no one was left behind.
          </p>

          <p>
            <strong>Professional Fire-Fighting and Fire Control:</strong> Every employee
            proficiently used fire extinguishers, followed the operation steps of
            "lift, pull, hold, squeeze", and accurately put out the fire at the root
            of the "fire source", quickly controlling the spread of the "fire".
          </p>

          <p>
            After the drill, Lu Liangjun, the company's safety supervisor,
            summarized the activity: "This fire drill has tested the feasibility
            of the company's emergency plan and the coordination ability of the
            emergency team. In the future, the company will continue to improve
            the safety management system and conduct various regular safety
            drills."
          </p>

          <p>
            The successful holding of this fire safety drill has not only
            improved all employees' awareness of fire prevention and emergency
            response capabilities, but also strengthened the coordination
            mechanism among various departments of the company.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-12">
          <a
            href={`${base}news`}
            class="text-sm font-medium text-blue-link hover:underline"
            >← Back to News</a
          >
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>

    <GetInTouchBanner client:visible />
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
